timing_case_an...is_propagation(25.10)  timing_case_an...is_propagation(25.10)

Name
       timing_case_analysis_propagation

Syntax
       timing_case_analysis_propagation

       {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables case analysis propagation.

       The  timing_case_analysis_propagation  global variable is the top-level
       control for enabling or disabling all case propagation in  the  current
       session.  When  set to true, case propagation will be enabled and other
       global variables can then be used to selectively control case  propaga-
       tion  in specific circumstances.   The timing_case_analysis_for_sequen-
       tial_propagation global variable can be used to control whether case is
       propagated across sequential devices.  Propagation  through  integrated
       clock-gating  (ICG) cells can be controlled with the timing_case_analy-
       sis_for_icg_propagation global variable.

       When set to false, the software disables case analysis propagation.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

